              },
              "free_text": [
                " the MC50 cyclotron of the Korea",
                "Institute of Radiological and Medical Science"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A high purity (>99.99%) Ag foil with a natural",
                "isotopic composition (107Ag 51.839% and 109Ag",
                "48.161%) was used as the target. Several foils of",
                "silver (50 mm thick), copper (100 mm thick), and",
                "aluminum (100 mm thick) with a natural isotopic",
                "composition were assembled in a stack.",
                "The Cu and the Al foils were used to monitor",
                "the beam intensity and to degrade energy, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " stacked-foil activation technique",
                "combined with high-resolution gamma-ray spectroscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " n-type coaxial ORTEC (PopTop, Gmx20) high-purity",
                "germanium (HPGe) detector with a diameter of 55.1 mm",
                "and a thickness of 52.2 mm. The energy resolution of",
                "the detector was 1.90 keV at a full width half",
                "maximum (FWHM) for the 1332.5-keV peak of 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-24",
                        "target": "13-AL-27",
                        "projectile": "P",
                        "process": "X",
                        "product": "11-NA-24",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "   In order to accurately measure the beam flux,",
                "   an Al foil (200 mu-m thickness) was placed at the",
                "   front position of the stack where the beam energy is",
                "   well defined."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-62,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-62,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-62",
                        "target": "29-CU-0",
                        "projectile": "P",
                        "process": "X",
                        "product": "30-ZN-62",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "   Monitor foils of copper (>99.98% purity and",
                "   50-mu-m thickness) and energy degrader foils of",
                "   aluminum (99.999% purity and  100-mu-m thickness)",
                "   and several foils of natural tin (Sn) were",
                "   inserted in the stack."
              ]
            }
          ],
